# CrowdSync — Smart Stadium Experience Application

A complete smart stadium application that enhances physical event experiences by addressing crowd congestion, long wait times, navigation difficulties, and lack of real-time coordination.

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph Frontend["Frontend (Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS)"]
        D[Dashboard] --> SM[Stadium Map + Heatmap]
        D --> QS[Queue Screen]
        D --> FO[Food Ordering]
        D --> EP[Emergency Panel]
        D --> NP[Notifications]
        D --> PR[Profile]
    end

    subgraph Backend["Backend (Node.js + Express)"]
        API[REST API Layer] --> CWD[Crowd Controller]
        API --> NAV[Navigation Controller]
        API --> QUE[Queue Controller]
        API --> FOD[Food Controller]
        API --> EMG[Emergency Controller]
        API --> USR[User Controller]
    end

    subgraph Realtime["Real-time Layer"]
        WS[Socket.io WebSocket Server]
    end

    subgraph Data["Data Layer (SQLite)"]
        DB[(SQLite Database)]
    end

    Frontend <-->|REST API| Backend
    Frontend <-->|WebSocket| Realtime
    Backend --> Data
    Realtime --> Data
```

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Rationale |
|-------|-----------|-----------|
| **Backend** | Node.js + Express | Fast API development, great ecosystem |
| **Database** | SQLite (via better-sqlite3) | Zero-config, runs locally, no external DB needed |
| **Real-time** | Socket.io | Bidirectional WebSocket for live heatmaps/notifications |
| **Frontend** | Vanilla HTML + CSS + JS | Per project guidelines, rich aesthetics |
| **Maps/Heatmaps** | Canvas API + custom rendering | No external dependency, full control |
| **Icons** | Lucide Icons (CDN) | Modern, consistent iconography |
| **Fonts** | Inter (Google Fonts) | Clean, modern typography |

## Proposed Changes

Work is organized into 4 phases matching the 4 agent roles.

---

### Phase 1 — Architecture & Data Design (Agent 1)

#### [NEW] Project scaffolding & configuration

- `package.json` — project metadata, scripts, dependencies
- `.env` — environment config (PORT, DB path, JWT secret)
- `README.md` — project documentation

#### [NEW] [database/schema.sql](file:///c:/Users/akank/Downloads/crowdsync/database/schema.sql)
SQLite schema defining all tables:

**Users** — `id, name, email, password_hash, seat_section, seat_row, seat_number, avatar_url, role, created_at`

**Zones** — `id, name, type (gate/concourse/stand/restroom/food_court), capacity, current_occupancy, coordinates_json, floor`

**Crowd Data** — `id, zone_id, timestamp, density_level (0-100), movement_direction, sensor_count`

**Queue Status** — `id, zone_id, facility_name, current_wait_minutes, queue_length, status, updated_at`

**Food Vendors** — `id, name, zone_id, cuisine_type, is_open, avg_prep_minutes, image_url`

**Menu Items** — `id, vendor_id, name, description, price, category, image_url, is_available`

**Orders** — `id, user_id, vendor_id, items_json, total_price, status (pending/preparing/ready/picked_up), estimated_ready, created_at`

**Emergency Alerts** — `id, user_id, type (medical/fire/security/lost_child), location_zone_id, description, status, priority, created_at, resolved_at`

**Notifications** — `id, user_id, title, message, type, is_read, created_at`

#### [NEW] [docs/api-spec.md](file:///c:/Users/akank/Downloads/crowdsync/docs/api-spec.md)
API endpoint documentation for all routes.

---

### Phase 2 — Backend Development (Agent 2)

#### [NEW] Server & middleware

- `server.js` — Express server + Socket.io setup, CORS, middleware
- `middleware/auth.js` — JWT authentication middleware
- `database/init.js` — Database initialization + seed data

#### [NEW] API Routes & Controllers

| File | Endpoints |
|------|-----------|
| `routes/users.js` | POST `/register`, POST `/login`, GET `/profile`, PUT `/profile` |
| `routes/crowd.js` | GET `/zones`, GET `/zones/:id`, GET `/heatmap`, WS `crowd:update` |
| `routes/navigation.js` | GET `/navigate?from=&to=`, GET `/routes/optimal`, GET `/nearby/:type` |
| `routes/queues.js` | GET `/queues`, GET `/queues/:zoneId`, WS `queue:update` |
| `routes/food.js` | GET `/vendors`, GET `/vendors/:id/menu`, POST `/orders`, GET `/orders/:id`, PUT `/orders/:id/status` |
| `routes/emergency.js` | POST `/emergency`, GET `/emergency/active`, PUT `/emergency/:id/resolve` |
| `routes/notifications.js` | GET `/notifications`, PUT `/notifications/:id/read`, WS `notification:new` |

#### [NEW] Real-time simulation engine

- `services/simulator.js` — Generates realistic crowd density fluctuations, queue changes, and order status updates on timers to make the demo feel alive

#### [NEW] Smart navigation algorithm

- `services/navigation.js` — Dijkstra-based pathfinding across stadium zones, factoring in current crowd density to suggest least-congested routes

---

### Phase 3 — Frontend Development (Agent 3)

All frontend files in `public/` served statically by Express.

#### [NEW] Core layout & design system

- `public/index.html` — SPA shell with sidebar navigation, glass-morphism dark theme
- `public/css/index.css` — Complete design system: CSS variables, animations, glass cards, gradients, responsive grid
- `public/js/app.js` — SPA router, Socket.io client, API helper, notification manager

#### [NEW] Pages/Screens (each a JS module)

| File | Screen | Key Features |
|------|--------|--------------|
| `public/js/pages/dashboard.js` | Dashboard | Live stats cards, mini heatmap, recent alerts, quick actions |
| `public/js/pages/stadium-map.js` | Stadium Map | Interactive SVG stadium, canvas heatmap overlay, zone details on click |
| `public/js/pages/queues.js` | Queue Tracker | Live wait times, progress bars, trends, facility filters |
| `public/js/pages/food-order.js` | Food Ordering | Vendor cards, menu with cart, order tracking with status timeline |
| `public/js/pages/emergency.js` | Emergency Panel | One-tap emergency buttons, active alerts list, status tracking |
| `public/js/pages/notifications.js` | Notifications | Grouped notification feed, mark read, real-time toast notifications |
| `public/js/pages/profile.js` | Profile | User info, seat assignment, order history, preferences |

#### Design Aesthetic
- **Dark theme** with deep navy/slate background (`#0a0e1a`)
- **Glassmorphism** cards with backdrop blur and subtle borders
- **Accent gradients** — cyan-to-purple for primary, amber for warnings, red for emergencies
- **Micro-animations** — card hover lifts, progress bar pulses, skeleton loaders
- **Responsive** — works on mobile and desktop

---

### Phase 4 — Integration & Testing (Agent 4)

- Wire all frontend pages to real backend APIs
- Ensure WebSocket events update UI in real-time
- Test all user flows end-to-end:
  - Registration → Login → Dashboard
  - View heatmap → Navigate to zone
  - Check queue → Order food → Track order
  - Trigger emergency → View alert → Resolve
- Fix bugs, polish animations, ensure data consistency
- Final project cleanup and README

---

